  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Patients with a diagnosis of schizophrenia or schizoaffective disorder, currently
        experiencing an exacerbation of symptoms (a score &gt; 20 for PANSS-Positive subscale),
        currently taking antipsychotics and who have given informed consent to participate.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        History of hypertension or current resting systolic blood pressure greater than 140 mmHg or
        diastolic blood pressure greater than 90 mmHg. Relevant medical illness (renal, hepatic,
        cardiac), prior history of intolerance to sodium nitroprusside, presence of a seizure
        disorder, any change in psychotropic medication in previous 6 weeks, diagnosis of substance
        abuse, pregnancy (as determined by urine test) or breastfeeding.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
